<article id="node-16985">
<h1 >3.4.5.10 Qualification for PLS</h1>
<h2>Summary</h2>
<p>This topic explains the qualification criteria for <a href="../guide-social-security-law/acronyms#pls" title="Pension loans scheme">PLS</a>, and the following relevant issues:</p>
<ul><li>who is likely to be eligible,</li>
<li>income reduced rate,</li>
<li>application of hardship, and</li>
<li>claims from overseas.</li>
</ul><h2>Qualification (<a href="../guide-social-security-law/1/1/q/10">1.1.Q.10</a>) criteria</h2>
<p>To qualify for PLS, a person must meet ALL of the criteria listed in the following table. If more detail about a criterion is required, the second column indicates where you will find this.</p>
<table><thead><tr><th scope="col">Criterion</th>
<th scope="col">More Detail</th>
</tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Be of age pension age OR the partner of someone who is, AND</td>
<td>-</td>
</tr><tr><td>Be receiving or be qualified for:
<ul><li>age pension,</li>
<li>disability support pension,</li>
<li>wife pension,</li>
<li>carer payment,</li>
<li>widow B pension, or</li>
<li>bereavement allowance, AND</li>
</ul></td>
<td>
<p>This topic</p>
</td>
</tr><tr><td>Own real estate in Australia of sufficient value to secure the payment of any debt that may become payable.</td>
<td><a href="../guide-social-security-law/3/4/5/20">3.4.5.20</a> Security for PLS</td>
</tr></tbody></table><div class="reference">
<p><strong>Act reference:</strong> <a href="https://www.legislation.gov.au/Series/C2004A04121" title="Social Security Act 1991">SSAct</a> section 23(5A) to (5D) Pension age, section 1133 Qualification for participation in PLS</p>
</div>
<h2>Who is likely to be eligible?</h2>
<p>The following groups of people may be receiving or qualified for some pension:</p>
<ul><li>all part rate pensioners of age pension age and their partners, being paid under either the income or the assets test, AND</li>
<li>people who WOULD have some pension payable under either the income OR the assets test, but for the rule that the lower of the 2 rates must apply.</li>
</ul><div class="example">
<p><strong>Example:</strong> Age would not be payable to a person who qualifies for the following:</p>
<ul><li>$20.00 per fortnight (pf) under the income test but NIL payable under the assets test, or</li>
<li>$30.00 pf under the assets test but NIL payable under the income test.</li>
</ul><p>As there is an entitlement under one of the tests however, the person satisfies this criterion for a loan under PLS.</p>
</div>
<p>The person needs to meet ALL of the qualification criteria for the pension to qualify for PLS.</p>
<div class="example">
<p><strong>Example:</strong> A pensioner who is receiving or qualified for Age needs to satisfy SSAct section 66 in regard to claiming <a href="../guide-social-security-law/acronyms#cfp" title="Comparable foreign payment">CFP</a>s.</p>
</div>
<h2>Reduced rate of pension - direct deduction</h2>
<p>If a pensioner is receiving a reduced rate of pension solely because of a direct deduction, they are NOT entitled to receive payments under PLS.</p>
<div class="example">
<p><strong>Example:</strong> Direct deduction could be due to a reciprocal agreement, proportional portability or compensation.</p>
</div>
<div class="example">
<p><strong>Explanation:</strong> The person is not considered to be on an income-reduced rate as defined in SSAct section 1133AA(1).</p>
</div>
<div class="reference">
<p><strong>Act reference:</strong> <a href="https://www.legislation.gov.au/Series/C2004A04121" title="Social Security Act 1991">SSAct</a> section 1133AA(1) PLS definitions</p>
</div>
<h2>Hardship</h2>
<p>PLS does not preclude people from consideration under the hardship provisions. It may be appropriate to investigate whether a pensioner has entitlement under the hardship provisions before proceeding with a request for payment under PLS. The legislation clearly provides, however, that the 2 provisions are mutually exclusive and that payment can only be made under one or the other provision.</p>
<div class="reference">
<p><strong>Policy reference:</strong> SS Guide <a href="../guide-social-security-law/4/6/7/10">4.6.7.10</a> General Provisions for Hardship</p>
</div>
<h2>Claims from overseas</h2>
<p>It is important that people overseas applying for PLS are aware of the terms and conditions of PLS.</p>
<div class="example">
<p><strong>Example:</strong> A delegate may need to conduct phone interviews or use the services of the diplomatic post overseas.</p>
</div>
<p>Generally, requests to be paid under PLS will not be successful from residents of non-agreement countries, who are currently not in receipt of the relevant social security payment.</p>
<div class="example">
<p><strong>Explanation:</strong> The claim for the relevant social security payment will be rejected if the person is either not an Australian resident and/or in Australia on the day on which the claim is lodged. Subsequently the PLS claim will also be rejected.</p>
</div>
